<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        SHEET METAL REPAIRS - REMOVE SPOT WELDS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REMOVE SPOT WELDS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Obtain a 3/8 inch (9.53mm) diameter sheet metal drill bit. Sheet metal drills can be
                obtained from your local tool supplier or a regular drill bit can be reground to a sheet metal point as
                shown in
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600664">Figure 64</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600664" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600664" filename="../figg16/G1600664.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 64. Sheet Metal Drill Bit</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PILOT HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SHEET METAL POINT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DRILL BIT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the pilot holes drilled previously, drill out spot welds along the windshield fence
                (edge) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600665">Figure 65</hotlnk>). Drill through outer panel only.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600665" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600665" filename="../figg16/G1600665.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Drilling Out Spot Welds</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. WINDSHIELD FENCE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. OUTER PANEL</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
